Following the central nave, the work is located in the cavity under the Baldacchino, while at the top rises the michelangiolesca dome where the words of Jesus to the apostle are reported: “You are Peter and on this stone I will build my church, you are the keys to the Kingdom of Heaven.” >
Each element of the artistic picture is in its place, as in a constellation: at the bottom is the Confession, at the center the papal altar and above the declaration “celeste”. From Heaven to Earth. The deep sense of Confession comes from afar, from the Jewish tradition. Our “big brothers” > (as Pope Wojtyla called them) celebrate it with Yom Kippur (Festa dell'Espiazione). In the temple > the high priest pronounced the name of God symbolically pouring out the sins of the community on a goat (called atonement) sent to die in the desert. Another animal itself was instead swallowed and sacrificed to the Lord. As catechism explains, in Christianity the scapegoat is Christ embodied: He was crucified for the salvation of all. >
