AGI - Frontal convoy, this night, at 3.30 p.m., between a steering wheel of the Caserta police and a black Audi on which there were suspected criminals long-losted to ATMs in the territory. After warning the station, a second steering wheel intervened closing the road to the fugitives with which, precisely for this reason, the clash occurred.
&nbsp;
The thieves at that point walked even if the policemen, unconscious after the crash, tried to chase them before being carried out, because of injuries fortunately not serious, at the civil hospital in Caserta where they had a seven-day prognosis. To give the news, with a statement, is the union of Police Fsp.
&nbsp;
"They are alive by miracle - says Valter Mazzetti, secretary general of the union - the colleagues who, in Caserta, intervened after criminals had eradicated an ATM in the center ending involved in a frontal confrontation between their steering wheel and the Audi on which the suspects traveled. We express to them all our solidarity, hoping that they will soon be able to resign after the serious accident, but above all our esteem for the unwavering sense of duty that has led them to chase the criminals on foot following the crash between the cars. We can say aloud that few, perhaps none, boasts the professionalism and the will force of the Italian police. To which, however, unfortunately do not correspond the necessary conditions for their health to be protected to the maximum, and why their service is also carried out in the best conditions. In the center of a city like Caserta you can't get two Flyers out together, while there as in every other center it would take more than two, and this says long on the urgency to intervene increasing the organics and enhancing the presence on the territory, just as we ask for years and how the Minister Piantedosi and the Undersecretary Molteni in our meeting two days ago".
&nbsp;
"Rarely we manage to get out in service of control of the territory the second steering wheel - reports Francesco Di Domenico, secretary of the Fsp union of Caserta -, in general there is only once per turn. We turned to the Quaker who committed to strengthening the services to strengthen control of the territory. But more men are needed, miracles can't make them anyone. We trust that appropriate measures will soon be taken from Rome, because here, with such a difficult and dangerous work, is the life of our policemen who speak, as well as the right to security of people."&nbsp;
